.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::AppHandler \- NIP\-89 recommended application handlers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::AppHandler;
\&
\&    my $pubkey = \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32;
\&    my $app_pk = \*(Aqbb\*(Aq x 32;
\&
\&    # Recommend an app for handling kind 31337 events
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->recommendation(
\&        pubkey     => $pubkey,
\&        event_kind => \*(Aq31337\*(Aq,
\&        apps       => [
\&            {
\&                coordinate => "31990:$app_pk:zapstr",
\&                relay      => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&                platform   => \*(Aqweb\*(Aq,
\&            },
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Publish handler information for an app
\&    my $handler = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->handler(
\&        pubkey     => $app_pk,
\&        identifier => \*(Aqzapstr\*(Aq,
\&        kinds      => [\*(Aq31337\*(Aq],
\&        content    => \*(Aq{"name":"Zapstr","picture":"https://example.com/icon.png"}\*(Aq,
\&        platforms  => [
\&            { platform => \*(Aqweb\*(Aq, url => \*(Aqhttps://zapstr.live/a/<bech32>\*(Aq, entity => \*(Aqnevent\*(Aq },
\&            { platform => \*(Aqweb\*(Aq, url => \*(Aqhttps://zapstr.live/p/<bech32>\*(Aq, entity => \*(Aqnprofile\*(Aq },
\&            { platform => \*(Aqios\*(Aq, url => \*(Aqcom.zapstr:///<bech32>\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Add a client tag to any event (MAY)
\&    my $tag = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->client_tag(
\&        name       => \*(AqMy Client\*(Aq,
\&        coordinate => "31990:$app_pk:my\-client",
\&        relay      => \*(Aqwss://relay1\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse a recommendation or handler event
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->event_kind;  # \*(Aq31337\*(Aq
\&
\&    # Query filters for discovery
\&    my $filter = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->recommendation_filter(
\&        event_kind => \*(Aq31337\*(Aq,
\&        authors    => [$pubkey],
\&    );
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-89 recommended application handlers. This NIP provides a way
to discover applications that can handle unknown event kinds through two
event types:
.IP "\fBRecommendations\fR (kind 31989)" 4
.IX Item "Recommendations (kind 31989)"
Addressable events where a user recommends one or more applications for
handling a specific event kind. The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag contains the supported event
kind, and \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags reference handler information events.
.IP "\fBHandler information\fR (kind 31990)" 4
.IX Item "Handler information (kind 31990)"
Addressable events published by applications describing how to redirect
users. Contains \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tags for supported event kinds and platform\-specific
URL templates with \f(CW\*(C`<bech32>\*(C'\fR placeholders that clients replace
with NIP\-19\-encoded entities.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::AppHandler\*(C'\fR object. Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 5
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->new(
\&        event_kind => \*(Aq31337\*(Aq,
\&        apps       => [],
\&        kinds      => [1, 30023],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Accepted fields: \f(CW\*(C`event_kind\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`kinds\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR),
\&\f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(Aq\*(Aq\fR), \f(CW\*(C`apps\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR),
\&\f(CW\*(C`platforms\*(C'\fR (defaults to \f(CW\*(C`[]\*(C'\fR). Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS recommendation
.IX Subsection "recommendation"
.Vb 11
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->recommendation(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,           # required
\&        event_kind => \*(Aq31337\*(Aq,               # required (d tag value)
\&        apps       => [                      # optional
\&            {
\&                coordinate => \*(Aq31990:pubkey:id\*(Aq,  # required
\&                relay      => \*(Aqwss://...\*(Aq,        # optional (SHOULD)
\&                platform   => \*(Aqweb\*(Aq,              # optional (SHOULD)
\&            },
\&        ],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 31989 recommendation Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`event_kind\*(C'\fR are required. Each app in the \f(CW\*(C`apps\*(C'\fR arrayref becomes an
\&\f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag. The \f(CW\*(C`relay\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`platform\*(C'\fR fields are optional but SHOULD be
included per spec.
.SS handler
.IX Subsection "handler"
.Vb 10
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->handler(
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,           # required
\&        identifier => \*(Aqmy\-app\*(Aq,             # required (d tag)
\&        kinds      => [\*(Aq31337\*(Aq, \*(Aq30023\*(Aq],   # required (k tags)
\&        content    => \*(Aq{"name":"App"}\*(Aq,     # optional (kind:0\-style JSON)
\&        platforms  => [                     # optional
\&            { platform => \*(Aqweb\*(Aq, url => \*(Aqhttps://app.com/<bech32>\*(Aq, entity => \*(Aqnevent\*(Aq },
\&            { platform => \*(Aqios\*(Aq, url => \*(Aqcom.app:///<bech32>\*(Aq },
\&        ],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 31990 handler information Net::Nostr::Event. \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`kinds\*(C'\fR are required.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR field is an optional stringified JSON object with kind:0\-style
metadata. If empty, clients should use the pubkey\*(Aqs kind:0 profile instead.
.PP
Each entry in \f(CW\*(C`platforms\*(C'\fR becomes a platform tag. The \f(CW\*(C`entity\*(C'\fR field is
an optional NIP\-19 entity type (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`nevent\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`nprofile\*(C'\fR). A platform
tag without an entity type is a generic handler for any NIP\-19 entity.
.SS client_tag
.IX Subsection "client_tag"
.Vb 5
\&    my $tag = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->client_tag(
\&        name       => \*(AqMy Client\*(Aq,                # required
\&        coordinate => \*(Aq31990:pubkey:identifier\*(Aq,  # required
\&        relay      => \*(Aqwss://relay.com\*(Aq,          # optional
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a \f(CW\*(C`client\*(C'\fR tag arrayref suitable for inclusion in any event\*(Aqs tags.
\&\f(CW\*(C`name\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`coordinate\*(C'\fR are required; croaks if either is missing.
Clients MAY include this tag to identify themselves. This has privacy
implications, so clients SHOULD allow users to opt out.
.PP
.Vb 6
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Event\->new(
\&        kind    => 1,
\&        pubkey  => $pubkey,
\&        content => \*(AqHello!\*(Aq,
\&        tags    => [$tag],
\&    );
.Ve
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses a kind 31989 or 31990 Net::Nostr::Event. Returns a
\&\f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::AppHandler\*(C'\fR object with accessors, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if the
event is not a handler kind.
.PP
For kind 31989 (recommendation), the returned object has \f(CW\*(C`event_kind\*(C'\fR
and \f(CW\*(C`apps\*(C'\fR accessors.
.PP
For kind 31990 (handler), the returned object has \f(CW\*(C`identifier\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`kinds\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR, and \f(CW\*(C`platforms\*(C'\fR accessors.
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that an event is a well\-formed NIP\-89 event. Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 31989 or 31990
.IP \(bu 4
Missing \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 31990 missing \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag
.SS recommendation_filter
.IX Subsection "recommendation_filter"
.Vb 4
\&    my $filter = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->recommendation_filter(
\&        event_kind => \*(Aq31337\*(Aq,
\&        authors    => [$user_pk, @follows],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Returns a hashref suitable for use as a Nostr filter to query for
recommendations for a given event kind.
.SS handler_filter
.IX Subsection "handler_filter"
.Vb 4
\&    my $filter = Net::Nostr::AppHandler\->handler_filter(
\&        event_kind => \*(Aq31337\*(Aq,
\&        authors    => [$app_pk],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Returns a hashref suitable for use as a Nostr filter to query for
handler information for a given event kind.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
These are available on objects returned by "from_event".
.SS event_kind
.IX Subsection "event_kind"
.Vb 1
\&    my $kind = $info\->event_kind;  # \*(Aq31337\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
The event kind being recommended (from the \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag of kind 31989).
.SS apps
.IX Subsection "apps"
.Vb 2
\&    my $apps = $info\->apps;
\&    # [{ coordinate => \*(Aq31990:pk:id\*(Aq, relay => \*(Aqwss://...\*(Aq, platform => \*(Aqweb\*(Aq }]
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of hashrefs describing recommended apps (from \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags of kind
31989). Each hashref has a \f(CW\*(C`coordinate\*(C'\fR key, and optional \f(CW\*(C`relay\*(C'\fR and
\&\f(CW\*(C`platform\*(C'\fR keys.
.SS identifier
.IX Subsection "identifier"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $info\->identifier;
.Ve
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`d\*(C'\fR tag value identifying the handler (kind 31990).
.SS kinds
.IX Subsection "kinds"
.Vb 1
\&    my $kinds = $info\->kinds;  # [\*(Aq31337\*(Aq, \*(Aq30023\*(Aq]
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of supported event kind strings (from \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tags of kind 31990).
.SS content
.IX Subsection "content"
.Vb 1
\&    my $json = $info\->content;  # \*(Aq{"name":"Zapstr"}\*(Aq or \*(Aq\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
The handler\*(Aqs metadata content (kind:0\-style JSON string), or empty string.
.SS platforms
.IX Subsection "platforms"
.Vb 2
\&    my $platforms = $info\->platforms;
\&    # [{ platform => \*(Aqweb\*(Aq, url => \*(Aqhttps://.../<bech32>\*(Aq, entity => \*(Aqnevent\*(Aq }]
.Ve
.PP
Arrayref of hashrefs describing platform handlers (kind 31990). Each
hashref has \f(CW\*(C`platform\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`url\*(C'\fR keys. The \f(CW\*(C`entity\*(C'\fR key is optional
and specifies the NIP\-19 entity type the URL handles.
